                     /note="Synthetic 13-residue epitope/affinity tag
                     GAPVPYPDPLEPR derived from M13 bacteriophage g3p (gene III
                     protein). It is the C-terminal detection/purification tag
                     of the pCANTAB 5E phage-display vector (Pharmacia/GE), used
                     to track and purify scFv-g3p fusion proteins and free
                     scFv/Fab fragments via anti-E-tag monoclonal antibody.
                     Conceptually based on the g3p-peptide epitope recognized by
                     mAb 10C3 (Beckmann et al., 1998). Note: this string is also
                     coincidentally present in human osteocalcin (UniProt
                     P02818); that match is unrelated to the engineered tag's
                     origin."
